This paper deals with the problem of spectrum sharing between WiFi and LTE-U systems, which falls under the domain of networked systems and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a fair time sharing model based on probability theory, which involves mathematical analysis and optimization, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely category. The paper also deals with the problem of coexistence between two different wireless systems, which involves system-level design and control, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category. The paper also discusses the issue of interference and security, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category. Finally, the paper involves simulation and performance evaluation, which falls under the domain of multimedia and human-computer interaction, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a less likely but still possible category.
